codex
I have enough context to code the verifier now. Plan: 1. write a standalone Paraspace pool/oracle scanner, 2. use only verifier-held collateral (including prefunded ETH wrapped to WETH) to exercise both missing-silo-check directions through `borrow()`, 3. report only the borrowed on-chain token balance delta, and 4. leave explicit code comments for the concrete no-collateral/no-profit case.
  → Write standalone FlawVerifier with direct-balance collateral discovery and Paraspace reserve scanning
  • Implement exact borrow-path validation for both borrow ordering cases and profit reporting
  • Compile locally in a temporary Foundry harness and fix any issues
codex
I’m writing the verifier as a single self-contained file now. It will scan the live pool for a real siloed reserve, source collateral only from balances the verifier actually holds, and then exercise both borrow orderings through the pool’s public `borrow()` entry.
